cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes an embedding approach to visualize and interpret the representation of data by RNN Seq2Seq models, which are commonly used in machine learning for translation or prediction tasks. The paper also demonstrates the effectiveness of the embedding method for unsupervised learning and clustering of spatiotemporal features. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as translation, it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, since the paper deals with recurrent neural networks, it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
